{
  "texts": [
    "Since the graph data structure is irregular, traditional data enhancement techniques in the image domain (e.g., image rotation, cropping, etc.)",
    "cannot be directly applied to graph data (Zhao et al. 2021 (Zhao et al., 2202)).",
    "To solve the problems of limited graph datasets, unbalanced data distribution, and over-smoothing in GNN, a series of data augmentation methods have been proposed, which are mainly categorized into nodelevel augmentation, edge-level augmentation, and subgraph-level augmentation (Yu et al. 2022).",
    "Table 5 summarizes the graph data augmentation methods.",
    "Node-level augmentation mainly consists of node dropping and attribute masking."
  ]
}